name: Icarus
description:
Bound to answer to your superior, stop your carrier right this sudden!
To cross this bridge to Lord's purified Heaven, 
Burning bright like Lucifer's wet dreams
You must chace away your sins this sudden
Come forth, closer to the woods, Lieutenant
Give way to your ego, crucified
In this judging moment, your truth,
You, brave soldier but, oh, so cruel all in the same damned moment
Confess! To your wax-riddled executioner,
You have before the son of Daedalus, 
It is I, Icarus! 
Beware my nuclear wings, on them your heart, 
Where i shall weigh them up and down with a feather from my love
Shall your heart burns you from inside out
Ready your might, for Icarus' flight!
